@NODE konfig "Requirements"

 This program needs not much to be happy:

   - MUI (I think at least 3.3)
   - OS 2.1
   - something to be scanned;-)

@ENDNODE konfig

@NODE install "Installation"

 The installation is very simple so haven't written an
 installscript, if you want to install it, just copy
 it in your prefered Drawer and if you also want to use
 the locale-features you'll have to copy the catalog-folder
 in the same directory OR your copy your prefered catalogs
 into the LOCALE:Catalogs/"Language"-Folder. And finally if
 you don't like the icon I selected, there are two other
 great icons of Eric Gerard in the Icons-Folder so you can
 select the one you like most.

@ENDNODE install

@NODE feat "Features"

   Why DirScanner?

      · @{B}Fonsensitive@{UB}!!!
      · You can scan more than one path at time!
      · You can search by name, size, date and comment.
      · Matching files can be directly started or viewed.
      · Bubble-Help
      · Shortcuts
      · It's FREEWARE!

   I think you'll find more reasons while using it!!!

@ENDNODE feat

@NODE anl "Manual"

 Okay, you made till the manual that's very gentle from you:-).
 But let's don't moon around:

 When DirScanner is started a nice about-requester appears but
 let's describe the interface:

 You can see two listviews, in the top one can be found the
 files that match your pattern that can be defined in the
 lower right corner (the string-gadget). The lower-left one is a
 list of paths that will be scanned for your pattern. The two
 buttons below this list explain on their own (do they?:-)),
 Below the pattern can be found two little cycles the use
 and sense of them is clear (is it:-)?). Finally I think it's
 wasted time to describe the function of the "Start"-button...

 But I think that I have to say something about searching by
 date because the date has to be in the dos-format, that means:

 DD-MM-YY.

 Valid dates:

   25-3-80
   25-03-80 (my birthday...:-))

 A invalid date:

   25-03-1980

 After starting the hunt, the left listview will be filled
 with the files that match the pattern if you doubleclick
 on one of them a inforequester will appear. Here are also
 two gadgets one tries to start the file and the other tries
 to view it using a viewer defined in the env-variable called
 SD_Viewer. If this variable isn't defined, DirScanner tries
 to use SYS:Utilities/Multiview. I think that's it. If you
 have questions, mail @{"me" LINK autor}!

@ENDNODE anl

